Part floors / Whole Floors / New Fitout

- New Spec Fitout
- Small Suites + whole floors available
- Staff amenities and services at your door step
- New destination controlled lifts

Central Plaza is a multi-tower commercial complex providing quality 'A' grade office space. The complex is prominently located offering two street frontages in the heart of the Chatswood CBD only a short walk to Chatswood's retail offerings including gyms, banks, restaurants and the access to one of the largest retail shopping precincts in Australia. Your staff will thank you.

In addition to the retail offering Chatswood is well equipped to provide services including child care, medical, banks, post office and serviced apartments for interstate or international visitors.

Chatswood has re-emerged as one of Sydney's most desirable workplaces - The busting heart of the Chatswood CBD creates the perfect location for large corporates and Central Plaza is just a 2 minute walk to the Chatswood transport interchange, a major transport hub. A high volume and diversity of surrounding retail and business amenities and open recreational spaces offer a great ambiance and staff engagement within this prime commercial precinct.

On arrival, the Towers provide an impressive entry due to the size and quality of the development and the buildings striking modern glass facade. Upon entering you will be impressed with the size of the lobby including the double height ceilings and corporate lounge area. All floors offer excellent efficiency due to the side core allowing exceptional levels of natural light and visibility across the floor. All floors enjoy large windows and natural light on all 4 sides ideal for an open plan work environment.

Area available from 208sqm - 2,130sqm and various floors with existing fitout in place.

Tower 1: Level 12 - 923sqm (existing fitout in place)
Tower 1: Level 13 - 879.5sqm (existing fitout in place)
Tower 2: Level 7 - 208.2sqm (brand new fitout being constructed including boardroom, one meeting room, one quiet room, 20 workstations, kitchen / breakout area)
Tower 2: Level 7 - 241.4sqm (brand new fitout being constructed including waiting room, boardroom, meeting room, one office, two quiet rooms, 22 workstations, kitchen / breakout area)
Tower 2: Level 13 - 879sqm (existing fitout in place)

We strongly recommend an inspection of this impressive commercial complex and take advantage of what Central Plaza has to offer and why this building has been leasing so well.

Inspection by appointment only.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Currently leased to Mortgage Choice, this well-presented mezzanine office space sits metres from Chatswood Interchange and offers excellent branding opportunities on both the ground and first floor. 

+ 120sqm*  
+ Fit out in place including bathrooms, kitchen, boardroom and offices
+ Air conditioned 
+ Exclusive entrance off Victoria Avenue with large glass windows, ideal for branding/signage (STCA)
+ Located at the base of a commercial office tower, opposite Chatswood Interchange (trains & buses) and only minutes to all the retail and food & beverage Chatswood has to offer 
+ Premises can be handed over with fit out in place or brought back to a shell
+ Parking available if required 

To arrange an inspection, please call Tom Bennett 0430 924 629 or Amy Pfeiffer 0401 198 401.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: OFFICE SPACE WITH HUGE EXPOSURE & SIGNAGE OPPORTUNITIES

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
A modern high tech industrial office/warehouse available for lease. This unit is conveniently located in the heart of the Chatswood industrial area. The property spans the cul-de-sacs between upper and lower Gibbes Street.


+ Located on the upper level of the estate, the unit benefits from excellent natural light to the office and production areas
+ Warehouse: 746.9sqm
   Ground - Office: 131.1sqm 
   Level 1 - Office: 212.4sqm
   Total: 1,090.4sqm
+ Ground floor showroom and mezzanine office with high clearance warehousing
+ Close to the Chatswood CBD and Train Station, providing excellent amenities
+ Close to Eastern Valley Way and Warringah Rd
+ Potential alternate uses: childcare, bulky-goods, play centre, rock climbing etc
+ Woolworths, SuperCheap, FortyWinks & Beaumont tiles have approved DA's to operate in the area
+ Warehouse benefits from large windows with views to Middle Harbour
+ 40ft container access
+ Ample on-site parking
+ Available now!
